Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.59,0:00:01.35,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:02.35,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.35,0:00:03.98,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,You've kissed someone before?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.44,0:00:06.25,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.27,0:00:09.22,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,S-So...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.22,0:00:10.48,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.01,0:00:12.15,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:13.40,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,On the cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.39,0:00:16.22,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just on the cheek?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.22,0:00:18.43,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,My little sister kisses my cheek a lot, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.43,0:00:19.95,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,On his cheek, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.95,0:00:22.16,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still a little jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:23.66,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Did I surprise you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.13,0:00:25.38,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:28.24,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me all kinds of questions \Nabout vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.24,0:00:29.48,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,so I did it as a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:30.84,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:37.01,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:51.07,ShowTitle,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Interviews with Monster Girls
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.70,0:02:11.31,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yuriko, I'm in love with—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.85,0:02:14.08,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Kyouko-chan, can you check \Nthe water in the bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:12.45,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.45,0:02:13.30,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.30,0:02:16.99,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's no good now... I can't be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.08,0:02:15.94,Default,Kyouko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:20.32,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I can't trust you anymore, Shun-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:22.69,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You have someone else now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.37,0:02:27.33,Title1,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(480,517)}The Dullahan Surpasses Space-Time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.69,0:02:26.41,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But it isn't me she loves. It's my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.41,0:02:30.03,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But you told me you loved her!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.00,0:02:30.96,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, the water's ready, so I'm turning it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.03,0:02:33.09,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Can you honestly say that wasn't true?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.96,0:02:33.09,Default,MOm,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.09,0:02:34.80,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Look me in the eye and say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.49,0:02:36.59,Default - italics,Kyouko,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari-chan said she kissed \NTakahashi-sensei
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.80,0:02:40.03,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The only one I really love is you, Yuriko.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.59,0:02:39.28,Default - italics,Kyouko,0000,0000,0000,,as a joke, to shake him up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:42.60,Default - italics,Kyouko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Sensei took it as a joke, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.03,0:02:41.30,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Shun-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.30,0:02:42.60,Default - italics,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yuriko...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.86,0:02:49.94,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, wouldn't it also be \Nokay for me to kiss him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.78,0:02:53.14,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I just need to carry these, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.14,0:02:56.41,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to make you do all the heavy work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.41,0:02:57.62,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,It's no trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:03:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a way, that's all I'm good for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.06,0:03:03.93,Default,Principal,0000,0000,0000,,He certainly does good \Nwork for us, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.93,0:03:04.80,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:09.22,Default,Principal,0000,0000,0000,,He's even taken the initiative to offer \Ncounseling for our demi-human students.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:11.48,Default,Principal,0000,0000,0000,,Their parents are fond of him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:13.60,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,That is true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.60,0:03:15.13,Default,Principal,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.13,0:03:16.12,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:22.61,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,That vice principal's such a jerk, \Nmaking me do all the heavy work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.61,0:03:24.93,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Being so beefy's getting to be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.93,0:03:26.26,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.89,0:03:27.81,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Machi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.14,0:03:29.64,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.74,0:03:33.21,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine. Thanks, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.42,0:03:41.15,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need... something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:47.10,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:49.28,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, nothing's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:50.70,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.96,0:03:57.46,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Is holding the head at eye level the \N"in" thing with dullahans now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:00.71,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, Machi's the \Nonly dullahan in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:02.80,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,She must have some specific reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.67,0:04:08.28,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,T-Takahashi-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.28,0:04:10.06,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:11.71,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,M-Machi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.16,0:04:15.09,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm carrying heavy stuff right \Nnow, so this is dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.09,0:04:16.81,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Let me finish carrying these first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.35,0:04:19.82,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there's a reason \Nyou want to play around,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.24,0:04:23.61,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,but it's dangerous to hold your \Nhead with an unstable grip—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.68,0:04:41.46,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:43.72,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't... hurt, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.45,0:04:46.98,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:49.46,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,That happens sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:52.69,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But surprisingly, I can always \Ncatch it pretty easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:54.02,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,So don't worry about—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:56.23,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You thought I'd see that and not worry?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.84,0:05:01.28,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, that pride could get \Nyou into a terrible accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.84,0:05:03.03,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Be more careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.50,0:05:14.25,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I... I didn't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:17.12,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:17.88,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.50,0:05:21.68,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,It's... It's my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:23.62,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I made this mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.62,0:05:24.95,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.61,0:05:30.85,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Machi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.87,0:05:33.68,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.54,0:05:48.50,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,And you can't straighten it while \Nholding your head, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.85,0:05:58.25,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Macchi? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.33,0:06:02.13,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.87,0:06:05.48,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,So Takahashi-sensei yelled at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.48,0:06:06.23,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.23,0:06:08.43,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You don't like being yelled at?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.43,0:06:10.61,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.61,0:06:13.04,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But it's more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.04,0:06:16.62,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-sensei is such a kind person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.62,0:06:23.48,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,So the idea that I got him angry \Nmakes me feel so awful...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.02,0:06:26.61,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I see... That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.50,0:06:28.13,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.13,0:06:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.56,0:06:32.32,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.88,0:06:33.78,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:37.25,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel, Kyouko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.78,0:06:40.59,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-sensei really is a kind person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.15,0:06:41.79,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:43.98,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.14,0:06:48.08,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,when we all ate those popsicles together?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.08,0:06:49.59,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:52.93,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried about my nature \Nas a snow woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.93,0:06:54.88,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,When I told Sensei about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.88,0:06:58.39,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,he tried something that actually \Nbrought out my nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:00.69,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, it wasn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:04.82,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand why he'd \Nput me through that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.82,0:07:07.34,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,But it cleared up my misunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.34,0:07:10.74,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,and gave me the chance to be \Nfriends with you and Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.74,0:07:12.69,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm really grateful to him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:14.53,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,So, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:18.47,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think being kind is only \Nabout coddling others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:23.75,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,He really cares about you, and he \Nwas honestly worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:25.14,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he yelled at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.24,0:07:28.80,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... Where are you taking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:30.78,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Just come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:33.39,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:38.81,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, this time, you two are \Ngonna have a real talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.73,0:07:44.31,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Your head can't run away \Non its own, Macchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:49.75,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... I guess, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.03,0:07:53.99,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Machi, I shouldn't have done \Nwhat I did. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:58.12,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Scolding students is a necessary \Npart of teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.74,0:08:02.26,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But there was no need to \Nscold you at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.26,0:08:05.25,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I just got too emotional and yelled at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.67,0:08:08.56,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I was partly to \Nblame for what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.56,0:08:10.80,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,We should have talked about it calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.13,0:08:12.55,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we can be friends again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.07,0:08:14.70,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.46,0:08:16.61,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.17,0:08:21.14,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't something you \Nneed to apologize for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.73,0:08:29.75,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:36.10,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's wrong, Machi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:38.36,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,H-H-Hikari-chan is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:38.95,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.94,0:08:45.42,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:50.20,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, I don't think getting too \Nemotional and yelling is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:54.85,Default,Testuo,0000,0000,0000,,You keep doing things that call for \Nscolding, despite constant warning!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.75,0:08:57.39,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:00.42,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want from me, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:01.56,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.79,0:09:05.23,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,If I tell him I was trying to \Ndo what Hikari-chan did,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.23,0:09:07.94,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,would it make Hikari-chan feel responsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:10.66,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:12.50,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Heh heh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:13.99,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,"Aha ha," what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.33,0:09:17.57,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,A-Aha ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.75,0:09:22.91,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:33.05,Eyecatch,,0000,0000,0000,,Interviews with Monster Girls
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.21,0:09:39.19,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you feel itchy anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.71,0:09:44.65,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I know Takahashi-sensei said otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.65,0:09:46.57,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,but what I did was wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.31,0:09:48.52,SignB,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari-chan, Yuki-chan, thanks for everything today. \N\NSince I made Sensei worry so much, \NI want to do something to make it up \Nto him. Any ideas? \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.31,0:09:48.52,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,To make it up to him, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:49.10,SignB,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Since I made Sensei worry so much, \NI want to do something to make it up \Nto him. Any ideas? \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:49.10,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,To make it up to him, huh... \N\NHow about a present?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:49.98,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,To make it up to him, huh... \N\NHow about a present?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.98,0:09:52.82,SignC,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a present? \N\NWouldn't that just make him feel bad again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:54.19,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that just make him feel bad again? \N\NYou think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.15,0:10:01.28,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,You think so? \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.15,0:10:01.28,SignB,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... \NI don't know about a formal apology gift. \NIsn't there anything else he'd like?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:05.16,SignB,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... \NI don't know about a formal apology gift. \NIsn't there anything else he'd like? \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:05.16,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's easy! \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:05.16,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one thing that he'd \Nlike more than anything else!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:05.87,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's easy! \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:05.87,SignC,Text,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one thing that he'd \Nlike more than anything else!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.13,0:10:07.16,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,One thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.50,0:10:12.92,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,T-Takahashi-sensei, would you like \Nto know more about my body?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:15.13,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I definitely would.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.45,0:10:16.47,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.47,0:10:21.10,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,that you can maintain vital functions \Nwhile head and body are separated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.10,0:10:23.68,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,is such a huge deviation from \Ncommon knowledge...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.68,0:10:24.81,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.12,0:10:28.77,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought meeting you, someone who \Nknows so much about demi-humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.77,0:10:32.56,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,might be a good chance to learn \Nmore about my own body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.38,0:10:35.77,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Should we ask for another opinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.77,0:10:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.75,0:10:39.54,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I majored in biology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.54,0:10:42.27,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Everything I know has its basis in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:46.68,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,So how about we ask someone who \Nhas a different kind of knowledge?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:46.33,SignA,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Musashino University of Science
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:51.50,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,College looks so different from high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:53.94,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,It's so big, I'd probably get lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.71,0:10:56.79,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it might feel that way at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.79,0:10:59.05,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're there, you get \Nused to it pretty fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.46,0:11:02.28,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Is the person we're seeing today \Na schoolmate of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:05.60,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,A schoolmate? Well, yeah, he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.60,0:11:09.69,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But after graduation, he stayed at \Nthe university to do research.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.23,0:11:12.79,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,He's a good guy, but he's \Na bit of an oddball.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.79,0:11:14.27,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,An oddball?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:15.10,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.10,0:11:18.26,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's what you'd call a prodigy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:22.53,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Souma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.47,0:11:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:26.45,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.45,0:11:28.44,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ha, Tetsu! It's been a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:32.21,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I see you still only have one expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:33.79,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,What was that pause, I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.18,0:11:36.08,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,And you must be Machi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:39.17,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Souma, a physics major. \NNice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:42.54,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,S-Same here... I'm Machi Kyouko.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.54,0:11:44.64,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for meeting with us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:47.53,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to be so formal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.53,0:11:49.06,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,He's just a weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:50.76,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! Harsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:52.89,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... However,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.34,0:11:56.36,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,meeting a real dullahan is quite an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.36,0:11:57.98,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.38,0:12:00.38,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,As a man of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:03.30,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,a dullahan is the very definition of romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.30,0:12:04.42,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Romance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:07.99,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed! For instance, let's say \NMachi-kun eats a steamed bun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:09.37,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,A steamed bun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:12.08,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Machi-kun puts the steamed \Nbun in her mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.79,0:12:11.58,BlackWhite,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H5218A3&\fs20}Steamed Bun
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:14.29,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,And when she swallows it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.29,0:12:18.05,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,it instantly teleports to her separate body!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.53,0:12:19.66,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,This is nothing short of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.66,0:12:24.01,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,proof that transportation of matter \Nbeyond space-time is possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.45,0:12:27.74,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Between Machi-kun's head and body, \Nthere's a high-dimensional tunnel...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.74,0:12:30.37,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, a wormhole, if I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:31.85,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,A wormhole?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:33.13,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I've heard of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.13,0:12:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In movies, they're the unexplained \Npassages spaceships use to warp?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.94,0:12:41.65,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, precisely. Occasionally called \N"hyperspace" in sci-fi works.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:45.11,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What's it actually like inside a wormhole?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:50.22,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,High-dimensional space is entirely \Nseparate from our space-time rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.22,0:12:51.08,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I can't definitely say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.65,0:12:54.53,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,but the wormhole that connects \NMachi-kun's head and body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.53,0:12:56.94,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,appears to be a fully established tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:13:00.09,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,After all, her nerves and blood \Nvessels are all connected,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.09,0:13:02.46,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,so it successfully fulfills the role of a neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:05.27,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,The role of a neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.27,0:13:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess it would have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:08.51,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.51,0:13:09.14,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,By which you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:12.42,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,This part of Machi... Her neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.42,0:13:14.78,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,The part you call a wormhole...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.78,0:13:16.96,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,It really does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:20.23,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,It exists, and it connects \Nher head to her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.25,0:13:22.19,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.19,0:13:24.30,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I'm not exactly sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.30,0:13:27.30,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But it's like her neck exists \Nin a separate space...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:29.54,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Like, her neck itself is the wormhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.54,0:13:30.78,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.23,0:13:35.29,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I don't doubt you, but on what grounds \Ndo you say this neck exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.60,0:13:40.64,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I think the fact that Machi talks \Nmeans that she has a neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:42.95,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Humans can't speak without vocal cords.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:45.00,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,So I asked Machi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.00,0:13:49.04,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, I was checked with an \Nendoscope, and they did find a neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:51.30,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I see! So you do have a neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:53.54,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Then, based on what things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.54,0:13:56.27,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,like endoscopes show, you're no \Ndifferent than an ordinary human.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:14:00.16,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's what the doctor said, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:03.69,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Though, that would be a \Npretty tiny wormhole...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:05.86,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! No, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.86,0:14:09.95,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,it could be said that Machi-kun's \Nwormhole is highly sophisticated!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.37,0:14:12.90,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,May I summarize?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.90,0:14:13.54,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.89,0:14:17.02,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Essentially, Machi-kun is no different \Nfrom an ordinary human,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.02,0:14:19.54,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,but her neck exists in a separate space,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:23.46,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,forming a wormhole that connects \Nher head and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.96,0:14:29.64,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, the separate space would \Nbe high-dimensional space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.64,0:14:32.43,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Theoretically, that'd make \Neven time travel possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:36.31,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I would love to see how it \Nworks with my own eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.12,0:14:40.40,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me for waiting until now to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.40,0:14:43.54,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,but what do the joints of \Nyour "neck" look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.54,0:14:46.23,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, both sides are enclosed in skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.23,0:14:46.82,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Skin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.12,0:14:48.87,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.87,0:14:51.14,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What goes in your mouth \Nends up in your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.14,0:14:53.78,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,but from outside, the pathway looks closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.78,0:14:57.25,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe someone's trying \Nto hide that pathway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:01.28,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Who would that mischief-maker be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.28,0:15:02.15,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:05.51,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,To say that someone's hiding \Nit is quite fitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.51,0:15:08.32,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,High-dimensional space definitely exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:12.51,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,but it's impossible to observe, \Nalmost as if someone is hiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.05,0:15:15.83,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Once food enters her mouth, the process \Nworks like any human's,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.83,0:15:17.93,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,and from outside, it's closed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:20.73,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't it be observed? \NWas that someone's intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.04,0:15:22.73,Default - italics,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Intention... Observation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:26.55,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Souma-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:27.53,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Machi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.53,0:15:28.61,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:32.77,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Is Souma-sensei thinking right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.77,0:15:33.78,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:37.49,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,His expression never changes, so it's \Nalmost like time's stopped, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.49,0:15:39.50,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,He really is unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:40.47,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.36,0:15:46.56,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess unusual people are unusual, \Nwhether they're demis or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:47.46,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.92,0:15:53.76,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,All phenomena occur for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.17,0:15:55.72,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,In physics, long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.72,0:15:59.35,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,observation wasn't considered a \Nsufficient cause of phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.74,0:16:00.80,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Observation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.80,0:16:03.33,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, whether humans \Nsee something or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.33,0:16:04.31,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Or to take it further,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.31,0:16:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whether humans exist in this universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.49,0:16:11.14,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,The results of phenomena \Nwould be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.14,0:16:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:14.74,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,That seems like an obvious \Nconclusion to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.08,0:16:16.50,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,But wait just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.50,0:16:20.04,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Some circumstances change \Ndue to human observation!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:21.91,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What would those be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.27,0:16:24.93,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,In a world where a single electron \Ncan be observed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.93,0:16:26.42,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,there's a thing called a "quantum"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.45,0:16:32.29,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Before it is observed, a quantum expands \Nlike space, in a wave-like pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.29,0:16:36.72,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,However, when observed, it instantly \Ncontracts into particles!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.12,0:16:38.42,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:39.66,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Particles?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.34,0:16:42.56,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.56,0:16:44.13,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:47.69,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,We'll save the good reactions \Nfor another time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.10,0:16:52.94,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, I'm trying to say that the act \Nof observation has its own meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.44,0:16:55.40,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,In terms of the phenomena I spoke of,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.40,0:16:59.57,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,human observation can change \Nthe result of a phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:02.95,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Does it not give you a sense of the \Nnecessity of humans in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.95,0:17:03.89,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.89,0:17:05.42,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,That is impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.42,0:17:07.64,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,And what is observation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.64,0:17:08.73,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,An act!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.73,0:17:11.46,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Behind every act is human intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:14.80,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, human intention \Ninfluences all phenomena!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.06,0:17:16.00,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.00,0:17:17.67,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a supernatural ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.67,0:17:21.18,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,And that's what came to mind \Nafter I spoke with Machi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.70,0:17:24.10,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I get it... By that logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:29.05,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,a snow woman's ability to freeze \Nmatter, using negative emotions,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.05,0:17:30.82,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,could also be called a psychic power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:34.03,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the joints of Machi-kun's neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:36.72,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, no trying to look in... \NIt's embarrassing for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.72,0:17:39.08,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,And touching it seems to hurt her, so don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.08,0:17:40.74,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! Blocked by her management!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.82,0:17:46.14,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, something far removed from \Nthe rules of our own space-time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.14,0:17:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be observable in that part of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.32,0:17:50.42,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,But a glance reveals it's covered with skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:52.24,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Who's hiding that something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:54.73,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, the answer is we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.73,0:17:58.15,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,When we try to observe a thing's existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.15,0:18:03.43,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,our intention to observe it causes \Na change in that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.70,0:18:06.72,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like what you said \Nearlier about the quantum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.72,0:18:09.06,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,More like I was just imitating that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.06,0:18:11.50,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, that flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:15.49,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it is not a flame, \Nbut a fluctuation in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:18.32,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,It's the only thing reminiscent of \Nan observable separate space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.80,0:18:21.96,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,And when someone tries to touch it, \Nan adverse reaction occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.96,0:18:25.60,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that its appearance \Nchanges with your emotions, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.60,0:18:26.82,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.82,0:18:31.96,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,That may be the proof that human \Nobservation influences phenomena!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:35.25,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Dullahans can perform relocations of \Nmatter that surpass space-time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.25,0:18:38.12,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,and they hint at the physical \Nsignificance of human intention!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.12,0:18:40.43,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,The dullahan is the potential of physics!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.42,0:18:42.48,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.48,0:18:45.10,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Good show. That was a lot of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.66,0:18:48.31,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Machi? \NDid you think it was fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.83,0:18:52.47,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,It was incredibly fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.71,0:18:57.28,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,How did you two get to know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.28,0:18:59.67,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,We sat next to each other in a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.67,0:19:00.28,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.98,0:19:04.26,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't changed. He's still a romanticist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.26,0:19:07.38,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to remove the "fiction" \Nfrom "science fiction."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.38,0:19:09.21,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! A funny way of putting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.81,0:19:11.54,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But you've changed, Tetsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:12.56,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Have I?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:14.96,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I see you, you look \Nmore muscular!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:16.64,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You meant my looks?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:20.26,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.62,0:19:26.64,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for doing this, Souma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.64,0:19:29.48,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. It was an intriguing \Nexperience for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.82,0:19:33.19,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But you want to look into what's \Ngoing on with Machi more?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.53,0:19:35.11,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.11,0:19:37.96,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,But you know better than \Nanyone how difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:40.28,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,researching demi-humans is, do you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:43.27,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Screw ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.27,0:19:46.22,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,If the subject's okay with it, \Nwhat's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.22,0:19:49.25,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! You sound just like you did \Nwhen you were a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:52.87,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I like this conservative \Nworld we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.43,0:19:58.71,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Souma-sensei said I shouldn't aimlessly \Naccept that I'm a dullahan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:00.10,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But watching him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:03.64,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,made me think I shouldn't go about \Nmy studies aimlessly, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.10,0:20:07.06,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,For me, studying is like taking a quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.06,0:20:08.64,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,There are problems, and I answer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.01,0:20:10.06,Office,Text,0000,0000,0000,,1st: Machi Kyouko \N\N2nd: Tachibana Aoi
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.64,0:20:10.06,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I was content with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.57,0:20:13.48,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But I was wrong. There's more beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.00,0:20:16.40,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Things that could change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:19.14,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,One of those things is the \Nsecret of dullahans,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.14,0:20:21.14,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,and I want to know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.14,0:20:26.41,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,If researching dullahans is difficult \Non an ethical level, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.41,0:20:31.85,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I could become a researcher \Nand research dullahans myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.69,0:20:33.62,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:35.33,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:36.26,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.26,0:20:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of a student gazing toward \Nthe future is so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.44,0:20:40.92,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:43.63,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,I have a pamphlet for our school here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.10,0:20:46.18,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You really intend to get involved, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:50.13,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay. I'll put in a good word.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.13,0:20:52.07,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I know very well
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.07,0:20:55.70,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,that you have a reason for being so \Neager to learn about dullahans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.70,0:20:56.61,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.61,0:20:59.09,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,If I can pinpoint high-dimensional \Nspace's behavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.09,0:21:01.84,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,warping and time travel may be possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.84,0:21:04.40,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I know human intention \Ninfluences phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:06.50,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,supernatural power isn't just a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.04,0:21:07.91,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yep...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:10.41,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention, if we knew \Nthe secret of dullahans,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.98,0:21:14.52,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,it may be possible for Machi-kun \Nto be a normal human.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.06,0:21:16.17,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.77,0:21:19.16,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that is possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.34,0:21:29.92,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.92,0:21:32.18,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,This is probably a "normal" look...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.35,0:21:35.88,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But it just doesn't feel right anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:42.10,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Those three would still be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.70,0:21:45.95,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Except that Machi would look \Nlike an older student.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.55,0:21:47.78,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.53,0:21:50.53,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Please hug my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.37,0:21:53.85,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Please put my head in your lap!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.59,0:21:59.66,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I guess ethics really are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.66,0:22:01.71,Default,Souma,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's Tetsu the responsible adult!
